WEBVTT

00:13.367 --> 00:16.266
[bright tone]

00:16.333 --> 00:19.266
[tense jazzy music]

00:19.333 --> 00:26.367
♪ ♪

01:46.133 --> 01:48.266
[thunder booming]

01:48.333 --> 01:50.867
- "Neither snow nor rain nor
heat nor gloom of night

01:50.934 --> 01:52.333
"stays these couriers

01:52.400 --> 01:54.633
from the swift completion
of their appointed rounds."

01:56.467 --> 01:59.266
So says the United States
Postal Service

01:59.333 --> 02:00.934
in their sunshine motto,

02:01.000 --> 02:03.967
adapted from the ancient Greek
historian, Herodotus.

02:04.033 --> 02:06.834
Now back then, swift could have
meant a year and a day.

02:06.900 --> 02:10.100
Now, it's 10:00 a.m.
the next morning, anywhere,

02:10.166 --> 02:11.734
from here to Cochabamba.

02:11.800 --> 02:13.934
People all over the globe
every afternoon

02:14.033 --> 02:15.133
stand at their mailboxes,

02:15.200 --> 02:17.367
wondering what
might be inside.

02:17.433 --> 02:19.100
You never know
what to expect.

02:19.166 --> 02:22.400
And in Oz, most times,

02:22.467 --> 02:25.066
the best part is
the expectation.

02:28.133 --> 02:31.166
[children playing]

02:44.800 --> 02:49.500
Prisoner number 99C124,
William Cudney.

02:49.567 --> 02:53.700
Convicted February 10th, '99,
murder in the first degree.

02:53.767 --> 02:58.333
Sentence: life, without
the possibility of parole.

02:59.333 --> 03:03.734
- She got an abortion behind
your back without telling you.

03:03.800 --> 03:06.333
- I forget
what abortion is.

03:06.400 --> 03:07.600
- It's when the baby
goes to heaven

03:07.667 --> 03:09.834
without ever gettin' born.

03:09.900 --> 03:13.333
So let me get this straight,
you aimed for the doctor,

03:13.400 --> 03:15.066
but you got
the son instead.

03:15.133 --> 03:17.533
- No, I aimed for the son.

03:17.600 --> 03:19.000
You took out
the kid on purpose?

03:19.066 --> 03:20.066
- Yeah.

03:20.133 --> 03:22.300
Now that doctor
knows how I feel.

03:22.367 --> 03:25.400
He killed my baby,
I killed his.

03:26.300 --> 03:28.066
- [scoffs]

03:33.467 --> 03:36.467
- What are you going to say to
him when you see him?

03:36.533 --> 03:38.100
- Who?

03:38.166 --> 03:40.867
- The doctor's son,
up in heaven.

03:42.734 --> 03:47.767
I already know what I'm gonna
say to Dr. Nathan's husband

03:47.834 --> 03:49.800
if they let me in.

03:57.600 --> 04:00.000
- Hey, where the fuck
have you been?

04:00.066 --> 04:01.900
Come on. We don't got
a lot of time left,

04:01.967 --> 04:04.033
put these on.
- No.

04:04.100 --> 04:06.300
- Cyril, don't start with me.

04:06.367 --> 04:08.100
- I don't want to box.

04:08.166 --> 04:09.133
I don't have to box.

04:09.200 --> 04:10.367
- Yeah, you do.

04:10.433 --> 04:13.166
- No, Mr. Cudney
said I don't have to.

04:13.233 --> 04:15.200
[eerie tone]
- Cudney?

04:15.266 --> 04:18.266
- Yeah.

04:18.333 --> 04:20.166
God doesn't
want me to box.

04:22.500 --> 04:24.967
- Okay,
no boxing today.

04:26.867 --> 04:29.433
- You're not mad?
- No.

04:29.500 --> 04:30.934
As a matter of fact,

04:31.000 --> 04:33.633
I think you should listen
to what Mr. Cudney says.

04:36.533 --> 04:38.233
It's okay, come on.

04:43.800 --> 04:45.667
- O'Reilly.

04:45.734 --> 04:47.166
Have you come to join
our prayer meeting?

04:47.233 --> 04:50.266
- Yeah.

04:50.333 --> 04:53.400
"Woe is me, this is a sickness
and I must bear it."

04:55.166 --> 04:59.400
First, you go and tell
my brother it's okay to box.

04:59.467 --> 05:02.333
Then you promise me
you never talk to him again.

05:04.400 --> 05:05.767
You got that?

05:08.667 --> 05:10.667
I never had much use
for the Bible before.

05:10.734 --> 05:12.433
You mind if I keep this?

05:12.500 --> 05:15.467
- No.
- Yeah, I didn't think so.

05:17.400 --> 05:19.633
- Hey, Gloria.

05:19.700 --> 05:21.200
- Watch yourself, O'Reilly.

05:21.266 --> 05:22.600
- Cocksucker.

05:28.000 --> 05:30.734
- Yo, Bricks.
- O'Reilly, you're the only one

05:30.800 --> 05:32.200
that get that shit right.

05:32.266 --> 05:34.233
- You checking out
the competition?

05:35.767 --> 05:37.600
- Man, they better pray.

05:37.667 --> 05:40.667
My man Bricks about to wipe the
canvas with them Muslim bitches.

05:40.734 --> 05:43.567
- I don't know, man. I saw Khan
working out in the gym.

05:43.633 --> 05:44.667
He's peak.

05:44.734 --> 05:46.400
- So's my nigga here.

05:46.467 --> 05:47.834
- Let's go get high.
- Ah.

05:47.900 --> 05:49.967
- Whoa. You think you ought
to be getting high

05:50.033 --> 05:51.300
the day of your first fight?

05:51.367 --> 05:53.300
- Shit, yeah,
I'm like Tyson, man.

05:53.367 --> 05:54.934
Know what I'm saying?
I party, then I fight.

05:55.000 --> 05:56.400
Then I party some more.

05:56.467 --> 05:58.033
[laughter]
- All right.

05:58.100 --> 06:01.133
See you guys.
- Hey, baby.

06:01.200 --> 06:04.800
Hey, Pancamo, put me down
for five Grovers on Khan.

06:04.867 --> 06:05.900
- That's a big bet.

06:05.967 --> 06:08.633
- I got money to burn, man.

06:08.700 --> 06:12.467
Hey, Hamid?
- Yes?

06:12.533 --> 06:14.166
- I just thought
you should know

06:14.233 --> 06:16.967
that Wangler's been talking
trash about you and Said.

06:17.033 --> 06:18.433
I think it's time you taught
that heathen homeboy

06:18.500 --> 06:19.433
a little lesson.

06:19.500 --> 06:22.000
- Don't worry,
I intend to win,

06:22.066 --> 06:24.467
in the name of Allah.

06:24.533 --> 06:27.800
Bismillah, ar-Rahman, ar-Rahim

06:27.867 --> 06:30.433
- Yeah, whatever,
just kick his ass.

06:30.500 --> 06:37.533
♪ ♪

06:45.734 --> 06:46.800
[laughs]

06:46.867 --> 06:50.066
Yeah, right.

06:50.133 --> 06:53.633
[crowd chattering]

06:53.700 --> 06:56.567
- Kenny "Bricks" Wangler!

07:10.266 --> 07:13.133
And in this corner,
Hamid Khan!

07:17.967 --> 07:19.166
Listen to me
at all times.

07:19.233 --> 07:21.133
Touch gloves
and go to your corners.

07:21.200 --> 07:23.467
Touch gloves and
go to your corners!

07:27.333 --> 07:28.900
Ready. Ring the bell, Lenny.

07:28.967 --> 07:30.500
[bell dings]

07:42.834 --> 07:44.633
- Hit the body, Khan!

08:03.633 --> 08:05.367
Hit the body, Khan!

08:17.133 --> 08:20.066
[dark tone]

08:20.133 --> 08:27.200
♪ ♪

08:29.100 --> 08:32.033
[dark, percussive tone]

08:32.100 --> 08:35.166
♪ ♪

08:35.233 --> 08:36.300
[bell dinging]

08:36.367 --> 08:37.667
- Hey, Bricks, nice one, man.

08:37.734 --> 08:40.100
You're like Tyson, all right,
Cicely Tyson.

08:46.800 --> 08:48.533
- A package
arrives unexpected.

08:48.600 --> 08:50.266
You open it.

08:50.333 --> 08:53.233
Sometimes it's a gift.
A bottle of vintage wine,

08:53.300 --> 08:54.900
let's say, from a relative.

08:54.967 --> 08:57.333
Sometimes it's
from the Unabomber.

08:57.400 --> 09:00.567
Innocent looking box,
and it goes boom.

09:00.633 --> 09:02.633
[ticking]

09:02.700 --> 09:05.066
- Yo, some Muslims
fucked with us,

09:05.133 --> 09:07.133
now it's our turn
to fuck with them.

09:07.200 --> 09:08.767
Let's go.

09:12.567 --> 09:13.734
- Yo.
- [whistling]

09:13.800 --> 09:15.133
Yo, yo, yo.

09:15.200 --> 09:16.467
I got a poem.

09:16.533 --> 09:19.800
- You said what?
- Shit, I got a poem, man.

09:19.867 --> 09:22.700
Ever since I got
back in Oz, right,

09:22.767 --> 09:25.467
I ain't been
writing no poetry.

09:25.533 --> 09:27.867
But I got inspired by something
I saw the other day,

09:27.934 --> 09:31.166
so this poem right here
is dedicated

09:31.233 --> 09:34.333
to Minister Kareem Said.

09:34.400 --> 09:37.533
[applause, shouting]

09:37.600 --> 09:39.033
[booing]

09:41.066 --> 09:45.400
That's it.
I figured you easy.

09:45.467 --> 09:48.734
All you want to do
is get your palm greasy.

09:48.800 --> 09:49.934
Capitalize.

09:50.000 --> 09:52.333
See, fuckin' America
been in your eyes

09:52.400 --> 09:56.333
for more than 450 years.

09:56.400 --> 09:59.767
And now you want to hide
your tears in your so-called

09:59.834 --> 10:03.533
Allah-given mission
to help your brothers.

10:03.600 --> 10:05.734
[crowd whooing]
Well, Allah gave me vision,

10:05.800 --> 10:08.166
and I'ma tell all the others.

10:08.233 --> 10:10.233
Talkin' about revolution.

10:10.300 --> 10:13.033
What I saw,
that was revelation.

10:13.100 --> 10:15.467
You frolicking
with the devil's maiden.

10:15.533 --> 10:20.033
[crowd exclaims]

10:20.100 --> 10:23.667
And now you happy 'cause now
you can manipulate her thing.

10:23.734 --> 10:24.967
Well, I'ma
put you on to something

10:25.033 --> 10:28.000
while we locked up
in here in this clink.

10:28.066 --> 10:30.600
Why you trying to get us all
to the heaven above,

10:30.667 --> 10:34.200
when she forget about
your contradictorial ass?

10:34.734 --> 10:36.200
Heh.

10:36.266 --> 10:40.100
Make sure you hide
them bloody gloves.

10:40.300 --> 10:43.333
[crowd exclaiming]

10:43.400 --> 10:46.333
[dark, percussive tone]

10:46.400 --> 10:53.433
♪ ♪

11:05.600 --> 11:06.800
- Allah--

11:09.433 --> 11:13.066
- This has gone from a private
humiliation to a public one.

11:13.133 --> 11:14.200
You disgraced us all.

11:14.266 --> 11:16.967
- You have a choice, Said.

11:18.200 --> 11:21.166
Her or us.

11:21.233 --> 11:23.967
You either promise you'll
never see that woman again,

11:24.033 --> 11:25.333
or you are finished.

11:31.567 --> 11:32.967
- Finished?

11:33.033 --> 11:34.800
- We'll choose
someone else to lead.

11:36.233 --> 11:39.734
[tense percussive music]

11:43.533 --> 11:45.133
- Patricia.

11:54.500 --> 11:55.767
Tell me what's wrong.

11:56.533 --> 12:02.800
- [sighs] I've been getting
these phone calls--

12:02.867 --> 12:04.467
threatening phone calls--

12:04.533 --> 12:08.133
demanding that
I stay away from you.

12:08.200 --> 12:11.033
- Stay away from me?

12:13.367 --> 12:15.367
- I saved the tape
from the machine.

12:15.433 --> 12:17.967
I thought maybe

12:18.033 --> 12:21.266
you might want it
or the lawyer, or somebody.

12:27.133 --> 12:29.834
- Did you change
your telephone number?

12:29.900 --> 12:33.166
- Well, yeah.

12:33.233 --> 12:36.700
But I--
I can't just move.

12:38.600 --> 12:40.700
What if they find out
where I live?

12:43.500 --> 12:46.467
I--I just don't understand.

12:46.533 --> 12:49.400
Why are they telling me
to stay away from you?

12:49.467 --> 12:52.166
- Don't you worry about that.

12:52.233 --> 12:53.400
I'll speak
with Zelman.

12:53.467 --> 12:55.633
He'll know best
how to handle this,

12:55.700 --> 12:57.834
how to protect you.

12:57.900 --> 13:00.700
- I don't want to stay
away from you.

13:04.633 --> 13:07.467
Fuck 'em.

13:07.533 --> 13:09.166
Oh, God, sorry.

13:09.233 --> 13:11.467
- No, you're right.

13:14.233 --> 13:15.900
Fuck 'em.

13:22.100 --> 13:23.400
Oh.

13:35.533 --> 13:37.266
Tell me neither of you know
anything about threatening calls

13:37.333 --> 13:38.934
to Tricia Ross.

13:40.900 --> 13:43.166
Tell me.

13:47.367 --> 13:51.266
Because whoever it was
will pay.

13:52.567 --> 13:54.934
In this life or the next.

14:04.734 --> 14:07.767
- [panting]

14:15.433 --> 14:17.400
When I got married,

14:17.467 --> 14:20.867
I got my wife's name
tattooed on my arm.

14:20.934 --> 14:22.834
That's pretty stupid, huh?

14:22.900 --> 14:25.934
Like a marriage is ever
gonna last

14:26.000 --> 14:27.734
as long as
a fucking tattoo.

14:31.800 --> 14:35.700
I told Shannon
that I wanted a divorce

14:35.767 --> 14:37.333
'cause of what
I feel for Gloria.

14:37.400 --> 14:39.467
[chuckles]

14:39.533 --> 14:42.633
I still love Gloria.

14:42.700 --> 14:44.533
And I try to fight it,
but I can't.

14:47.533 --> 14:49.667
She's under my skin, man.

14:51.767 --> 14:53.333
She's under
my fucking skin.

14:58.233 --> 14:59.567
- Come on, man.
Look, I beat the shit

14:59.633 --> 15:01.567
out that motherfucker.
- You had some fun.

15:01.633 --> 15:02.834
- All right?
- One love, one love.

15:02.900 --> 15:04.400
- Getting your ass whipped.
[laughter]

15:04.467 --> 15:08.000
- You ask us to help you take
out Wangler, Pierce, Poet.

15:08.066 --> 15:09.867
Then you say wait.

15:09.934 --> 15:11.667
- I don't want to kill them

15:11.734 --> 15:14.667
or there will be a war between
us and the other homeboys.

15:14.734 --> 15:16.433
I just want
to slow them down.

15:16.500 --> 15:17.834
- He's right.

15:17.900 --> 15:21.600
We got to make the deed
look like an accident.

15:21.667 --> 15:24.934
- Poet and Pierce first.

15:25.000 --> 15:26.767
I have my own plans
for Wangler.

15:29.300 --> 15:32.400
- Kenny.

15:32.467 --> 15:35.000
Kenny.
- Bricks, damn! What the--

15:35.066 --> 15:36.800
Bricks, man.

15:36.867 --> 15:38.800
- I need to talk to you.

15:38.867 --> 15:41.600
- What?

15:41.667 --> 15:43.834
- It's bad news.

15:45.300 --> 15:47.600
Your wife's dead.

15:47.667 --> 15:48.734
- What?

15:48.800 --> 15:52.900
- She was shot,
execution style.

15:52.967 --> 15:54.433
- Oh, shit.

15:54.500 --> 15:56.834
- That's too bad, yo.
- Word.

15:56.900 --> 16:01.166
Real sorrowful, Kenny,
real sorrowful.

16:01.233 --> 16:03.066
- There's more.

16:03.133 --> 16:05.233
- What?

16:05.300 --> 16:07.900
- She was found in the apartment
with another man.

16:08.000 --> 16:09.600
A Ronnie Smith.

16:09.667 --> 16:13.467
- Oh, man, Ronnie,
that was my boy.

16:13.533 --> 16:15.433
- They were found
in bed together.

16:19.066 --> 16:21.200
Look, I've, uh,
scheduled some time

16:21.266 --> 16:24.166
for you to see
Sister Peter Marie.

16:24.233 --> 16:25.800
- My baby, how's my son?

16:25.867 --> 16:27.734
- He's fine.

16:27.800 --> 16:30.233
He was at your mother's
at the time.

16:30.300 --> 16:32.000
- Amen.
- Thank God.

16:32.066 --> 16:33.667
- Anything I can do?

16:33.734 --> 16:35.066
- No, no, no.

16:35.133 --> 16:37.800
Look, do the cops know
who did this shit?

16:39.433 --> 16:43.300
- They think
it was drug-related.

16:43.367 --> 16:46.233
- Can I go to the funeral?

16:46.300 --> 16:47.333
- I'll see what I can do.

17:01.867 --> 17:06.900
[laughter]

17:06.967 --> 17:09.100
- Oh, man.
I thought I was gonna die

17:09.166 --> 17:11.700
keeping myself from laughing.
- Word.

17:11.767 --> 17:13.333
Hold up, wait, wait,
what about when I--

17:13.400 --> 17:15.867
what about when I
gave him this face?

17:15.934 --> 17:18.633
- No, no.
[laughter]

17:18.700 --> 17:19.800
Okay.

17:19.867 --> 17:21.367
But you wanted that bitch dead,

17:21.433 --> 17:23.066
and that nigga Ronnie dead.

17:23.133 --> 17:25.400
Now they dead.
- Mm-hmm.

17:25.467 --> 17:26.467
Who loves you, baby?

17:26.533 --> 17:27.967
- Y'all do, yo.
Fuck that.

17:28.033 --> 17:29.834
- Handled it right.
- Let's go get high.

17:29.900 --> 17:33.467
- Let's do it.
- Yeah.

17:33.533 --> 17:35.233
- Of course, any kind of letter
from the outside

17:35.300 --> 17:37.166
is a potential bomb,

17:37.233 --> 17:38.767
blowing up in your face
with memories

17:38.834 --> 17:42.066
of what life was like before
the gates slammed shut,

17:42.133 --> 17:45.967
before someone,
definitely not your momma,

17:46.033 --> 17:48.900
screamed, "Lights out!"

17:51.000 --> 17:53.133
Sometimes the sweeter
the letter,

17:53.200 --> 17:55.433
the more bitter the aftertaste.

17:55.500 --> 17:58.500
- [whistles]
- "My dear son,

17:58.567 --> 18:01.000
"I woke up today dreaming
of what life would be like

18:01.066 --> 18:03.700
"when you're free,

18:03.767 --> 18:05.867
"telling myself that every day

18:05.934 --> 18:07.934
"is one day closer
to you coming home.

18:08.000 --> 18:10.233
[tense percussive tone]

18:10.300 --> 18:13.200
"One day closer to us
being together again.

18:17.133 --> 18:20.233
"Everything here
is the same.

18:23.300 --> 18:25.266
"The neighborhood's
the same.

18:30.767 --> 18:33.333
"Even the faces,
everyone looks the same.

18:38.166 --> 18:40.166
"Is everything
there okay?

18:43.433 --> 18:45.500
"Is there anything
we can do?

18:49.967 --> 18:52.000
"We miss you.

18:56.100 --> 18:58.000
We love you."

18:58.066 --> 18:59.533
[music building]

18:59.600 --> 19:02.734
[screaming]

19:02.800 --> 19:06.066
[alarm blaring]

19:06.133 --> 19:07.567
- They need an IV
started right away.

19:07.633 --> 19:09.133
Water and glucose.

19:09.200 --> 19:11.800
[pained grunting]

19:12.867 --> 19:15.433
- I can't
stand the pain.

19:19.600 --> 19:20.533
- I didn't see a thing.

19:20.600 --> 19:23.600
- What about you?

19:23.667 --> 19:25.066
[beeping]
- Lockdown!

19:25.133 --> 19:27.400
Lockdown, lockdown!

19:27.467 --> 19:29.100
[indistinct yelling]
Get down.

19:29.166 --> 19:31.400
Lockdown.

19:31.467 --> 19:34.066
- Lockdown!

19:37.633 --> 19:39.834
[gate buzzes]

19:46.600 --> 19:50.166
[indistinct shouting]
[banging]

20:06.300 --> 20:07.667
- Jun, what up?

20:09.734 --> 20:12.300
Junior, why we in lockdown?

20:12.367 --> 20:13.600
Yo.

20:13.667 --> 20:16.600
[intense music]

20:16.667 --> 20:21.166
♪ ♪

20:21.233 --> 20:23.233
- Welcome back, Kenny.

20:23.300 --> 20:30.333
♪ ♪

20:31.200 --> 20:34.767
- Pity what happened
to Poet and Pierce.

20:34.834 --> 20:36.633
- They gonna live?

20:36.700 --> 20:38.500
- For now.

20:38.567 --> 20:40.433
But, you know,
life is fragile, man.

20:40.500 --> 20:42.600
- What about me?

20:47.767 --> 20:49.433
- How are you doing
in that program, man?

20:49.500 --> 20:52.767
You meet with, uh, Rivera yet,
face-to-face?

20:52.834 --> 20:55.333
- No. Just, you know, mostly

20:55.400 --> 20:58.233
talking to Sister Peter Marie.

20:58.300 --> 20:59.300
- About?

20:59.367 --> 21:00.867
- You know, this and that.

21:00.934 --> 21:03.066
- Well, Michael, as long as

21:03.133 --> 21:06.000
this doesn't connect
to that,

21:06.066 --> 21:07.200
you're safe with me.

21:10.433 --> 21:12.266
- I wanna warn you, Miguel,

21:12.333 --> 21:14.300
there's no way to predict
the outcome, emotionally,

21:14.367 --> 21:17.934
of facing Officer Rivera
or his wife.

21:19.133 --> 21:20.266
Yeah.

21:20.333 --> 21:24.100
When you blinded him,
you hurt them both.

21:24.166 --> 21:25.600
And they may have
no sympathy

21:25.667 --> 21:30.800
for any pain or guilt
you're feeling.

21:30.867 --> 21:33.433
So why don't you tell me
what you did to Eugene Rivera?

21:33.500 --> 21:34.934
- You know what I did.

21:35.000 --> 21:37.900
I don't know why we got
to waste time rehashing it.

21:37.967 --> 21:40.700
- We have all
the time we need.

21:40.767 --> 21:43.600
And it's very important to
articulate what you've done.

21:44.333 --> 21:47.133
So when was it?

21:49.700 --> 21:52.033
- It was last summer.

21:52.100 --> 21:54.467
- Why did you do it?

21:54.533 --> 21:55.767
- I don't know.

21:55.834 --> 21:59.000
You know, I was
all fucked up and shit,

21:59.066 --> 22:01.367
some stuff going on.

22:01.433 --> 22:03.033
And I got tense.

22:06.533 --> 22:08.633
I don't know, you know?

22:08.700 --> 22:10.300
I-it just happened.

22:10.367 --> 22:13.300
- What just happened?

22:13.367 --> 22:15.867
What did you,
Miguel Alvarez--

22:15.934 --> 22:18.066
- Shit!

22:20.200 --> 22:23.867
I, um--

22:23.934 --> 22:27.000
I cut his eyes really bad.

22:27.066 --> 22:29.367
- How bad?

22:30.300 --> 22:33.133
- Well, I stabbed him,
you know?

22:33.200 --> 22:36.934
I stabbed them, his eyes,
you know?

22:39.533 --> 22:41.367
The scalpel...

22:41.433 --> 22:43.700
[metal clanging]

22:43.767 --> 22:46.467
I--I dropped it.

22:49.467 --> 22:50.800
And when it hit the floor...

22:51.200 --> 22:53.033
[metal clanging]

22:53.100 --> 22:55.734
It made this ringing sound.

22:59.400 --> 23:01.700
- Okay.

23:01.767 --> 23:04.033
Would you like to sit down?

23:10.400 --> 23:13.367
Now...

23:13.433 --> 23:15.467
Why did you do it?

23:15.533 --> 23:17.500
- I already told you,
already.

23:17.567 --> 23:19.734
It's 'cause
of tension and shit.

23:19.800 --> 23:24.500
- No, Miguel.

23:24.567 --> 23:28.300
Why you did this,
something so deliberate.

23:29.400 --> 23:31.767
You're gonna have to
tell Eugene why

23:31.834 --> 23:34.667
and he's going to ask.

23:34.734 --> 23:36.834
- I will.

23:36.900 --> 23:39.333
- Then why can't
you tell me?

23:39.400 --> 23:42.066
- Because I don't
owe it to you.

23:42.133 --> 23:45.066
[dark, percussive music]

23:45.133 --> 23:50.000
♪ ♪

23:50.066 --> 23:54.300
- This is who I want to
sit down with, face-to-face,

23:54.367 --> 23:56.800
and ask why.

23:56.867 --> 24:01.200
- He's here now, Eugene.
- Really?

24:01.266 --> 24:03.767
So what's his answer?

24:03.834 --> 24:06.834
I don't hear his voice.

24:06.900 --> 24:09.433
All I hear is voices
that sound like my own,

24:09.500 --> 24:12.734
but they don't say
why Alvarez did this.

24:12.800 --> 24:16.600
They don't tell me
why I deserve it.

24:16.667 --> 24:20.734
- What happened
was not your fault.

24:20.800 --> 24:24.567
And God is not going
to answer your questions

24:24.633 --> 24:26.567
in a big, booming voice.

24:26.633 --> 24:32.700
He's going to answer you
through talking to Alvarez.

24:32.767 --> 24:36.133
So why don't you tell me
what you want to say to him?

24:36.200 --> 24:39.033
- I keep thinking someone
is gonna open a door

24:39.100 --> 24:42.066
and let me out
of this dark room.

24:42.133 --> 24:43.533
- What else?

24:43.600 --> 24:44.600
What else
do you want to say?

24:44.667 --> 24:46.600
- I can't,
not in front of you.

24:46.667 --> 24:49.333
- Come on.
I'm a big girl, go ahead.

24:49.400 --> 24:52.266
Whatever it is, say it.

24:55.800 --> 24:58.166
- I hate you, Alvarez,

24:58.233 --> 25:00.800
you fucking motherfucker!

25:00.867 --> 25:02.667
'Cause of you,
I got to carry around

25:02.734 --> 25:04.767
all this shit in the dark.

25:04.834 --> 25:07.767
If it wasn't for Tina, I would
have killed myself already.

25:07.834 --> 25:11.066
Sometimes I think I should
kill myself for her sake,

25:11.133 --> 25:14.233
so she could start
a new life without me.

25:14.300 --> 25:15.734
Some days, Alvarez,

25:15.800 --> 25:18.800
I wished you would have killed
me instead of doing this.

25:22.800 --> 25:25.200
I can't cry anymore.

25:25.266 --> 25:26.700
Did you know that?

25:26.767 --> 25:30.734
You made it
so I can't cry.

25:44.333 --> 25:45.467
- Junk mail.

25:45.533 --> 25:47.433
Selling you this,
promising you that.

25:47.500 --> 25:48.867
Publisher's Clearing House.

25:48.934 --> 25:50.700
You got your American
Family Sweepstakes.

25:50.767 --> 25:53.000
You got Ed McMahon warning you
to open that envelope

25:53.066 --> 25:55.166
because you could be
a millionaire.

25:55.233 --> 25:59.300
And you know you can never win,
so, uh...

25:59.367 --> 26:01.967
you toss it.

26:02.033 --> 26:04.000
But what if you made
the wrong choice?

26:05.033 --> 26:08.133
What if this was the
one-in-a-trillion time

26:08.200 --> 26:09.500
you'd win?

26:09.567 --> 26:12.300
[sighs] Man, this sexual
harassment thing

26:12.367 --> 26:14.266
is eating away at me.

26:14.333 --> 26:16.633
State settles
out of court,

26:16.700 --> 26:18.233
reinstates Howell
to her job,

26:18.300 --> 26:19.667
which implies my guilt.

26:19.734 --> 26:21.467
But I'm not fucking guilty.

26:21.533 --> 26:23.700
- You're a victim of
the times, my friend.

26:23.767 --> 26:26.400
Years ago, a woman complained
of workplace harassment,

26:26.467 --> 26:29.467
no one believed her,
no one even cared.

26:29.533 --> 26:32.266
Today, it's assumed that
every guy in every office

26:32.333 --> 26:34.166
is an ass-grabbing pig,

26:34.233 --> 26:36.066
which, of course, uh, we are.

26:36.133 --> 26:37.300
- No, I'm not!

26:37.367 --> 26:38.934
- Tim, come on.

26:39.000 --> 26:41.200
You told me you've fucked every
woman that worked in this place,

26:41.266 --> 26:43.400
except for
Sister Peter Marie.

26:43.467 --> 26:45.934
- Man, so I've slept around.

26:46.000 --> 26:47.800
It's always been mutual.

26:47.867 --> 26:50.033
I would never force
my way on a woman,

26:50.100 --> 26:52.133
use my position
to get laid.

26:52.200 --> 26:54.567
- Prove it.
- How?

26:54.633 --> 26:56.100
- Don't let
the state settle.

26:56.166 --> 26:57.500
Take her to court.

26:57.567 --> 27:00.834
Get Nathan and Wittlesey
and Sister Peter Marie

27:00.900 --> 27:02.367
to testify
on your behalf.

27:02.433 --> 27:04.433
You know, fight Howell.

27:04.500 --> 27:06.867
- The odds are against me.

27:06.934 --> 27:09.400
- When are they ever
in your favor?

27:10.600 --> 27:12.133
[gate buzzes]

27:12.200 --> 27:15.333
- For the media, this is
like a seven-course meal.

27:15.400 --> 27:18.467
- [sighs] Meaning, if I want to
take this any further,

27:18.533 --> 27:20.967
I better be prepared
to see my face on TV

27:21.033 --> 27:22.867
and in the headlines.
- Yes.

27:22.934 --> 27:24.567
And if the public
only half listens,

27:24.633 --> 27:27.100
only retains half of
what they read,

27:27.166 --> 27:29.333
the story will burn hot
for a few days.

27:29.400 --> 27:32.867
You'll look guilty at first,
regardless of the facts.

27:32.934 --> 27:34.600
Then the story will cool.

27:34.667 --> 27:36.767
By the time we win,
no one will know.

27:36.834 --> 27:39.500
But you'll have to carry the
stigma of those first few days

27:39.567 --> 27:42.533
with you for
the rest of your life.

27:43.767 --> 27:45.667
- Gloria,

27:45.734 --> 27:49.633
what have you heard about this
harassment case against Tim?

27:49.700 --> 27:51.867
- Claire Howell in Solitary

27:51.934 --> 27:53.600
says that Tim had her fired

27:53.667 --> 27:55.500
because she stopped
having sex with him.

27:55.567 --> 27:58.300
- Yeah, I don't
believe it.

27:58.367 --> 28:00.266
Do you?

28:00.333 --> 28:02.567
- No.

28:02.633 --> 28:04.066
- But?

28:04.133 --> 28:08.333
- I dated Tim, you know,
when I was separated.

28:08.400 --> 28:13.867
When it comes to sex
and relationships, he's--

28:13.934 --> 28:15.033
I don't know.

28:15.100 --> 28:17.367
I don't know,
today anything's possible.

28:17.433 --> 28:20.300
- Pete, Gloria,
I'm glad you're both here.

28:20.367 --> 28:23.533
I'm, uh, putting
together my case,

28:23.600 --> 28:25.800
and I'd like you both
to be character witnesses.

28:25.867 --> 28:28.166
- Sure.
- Thanks.

28:28.233 --> 28:29.433
Gloria?

28:29.500 --> 28:32.033
- Yeah,
I'll let you know.

28:32.100 --> 28:33.266
- What?

28:33.333 --> 28:34.834
You don't believe
Claire Howell, do you?

28:34.900 --> 28:38.500
- No, I just wanna talk
to her, hear her side.

28:38.567 --> 28:40.567
- Her side?

28:40.633 --> 28:42.467
What the fuck is
that supposed to mean?

28:42.533 --> 28:45.166
That you think what
she's saying might be true?

28:45.233 --> 28:46.667
Which means I'm lying.

28:46.734 --> 28:49.266
Which means you think
I'm capable of abusing women.

28:49.333 --> 28:51.433
- No, I didn't mean--
- Thanks a lot, Gloria.

28:51.500 --> 28:53.266
Thanks for the vote
of fucking confidence.

28:53.333 --> 28:55.133
- Tim, wait a--

28:59.500 --> 29:00.433
- Ahh!

29:00.500 --> 29:03.433
[intense music]

29:03.500 --> 29:10.533
♪ ♪

29:16.967 --> 29:19.567
Hey.

29:19.633 --> 29:21.900
How's Didi?

29:21.967 --> 29:23.967
- She misses her grandma.

29:24.033 --> 29:26.266
So do I.

29:28.300 --> 29:31.100
- We've got all manner
of men in here.

29:31.166 --> 29:35.834
Men who've raped women,
beaten them, murdered them.

29:35.900 --> 29:38.133
Ryan O'Reilly had
Gloria's husband killed

29:38.200 --> 29:40.633
because Ryan
loved her so much.

29:40.700 --> 29:43.834
I remember thinking at the time,

29:43.900 --> 29:47.000
such passion.

29:47.066 --> 29:48.967
Could I ever
feel such passion?

29:49.767 --> 29:51.934
- Tim.

29:52.000 --> 29:55.500
- You know, I was gonna fight
this harassment charge.

29:55.567 --> 29:59.000
I was going to ask you and
Gloria to testify on my behalf,

29:59.066 --> 30:01.533
build a case because
Howell is lying.

30:01.600 --> 30:04.133
I didn't force her
to do anything.

30:04.200 --> 30:05.834
- Well, why not fight it?

30:05.900 --> 30:09.066
- Because I am guilty...

30:09.133 --> 30:12.600
Of using her--her body.

30:12.667 --> 30:16.800
Of not giving
a shit about her,

30:16.867 --> 30:21.300
about her feelings for me,
about her feelings for herself.

30:21.367 --> 30:26.233
Now I know I did
the same thing to my ex-wife,

30:26.300 --> 30:29.266
and to Gloria...

30:29.333 --> 30:31.967
To you.

30:32.033 --> 30:34.266
[gate buzzes]

30:34.333 --> 30:36.400
[chuckles]

30:39.367 --> 30:43.400
Diane, if I asked you
to testify on my behalf,

30:43.467 --> 30:47.867
would you
have done it?

30:47.934 --> 30:50.200
- Sure.

30:50.266 --> 30:53.767
'Cause what
we had was real,

30:53.834 --> 30:55.867
if only for a moment.

31:06.367 --> 31:08.433
[tires screech]

31:27.367 --> 31:30.300
- Prisoner #99K871.

31:30.367 --> 31:34.867
Yuri Kosygin.
Convicted March 23rd, '99.

31:34.934 --> 31:37.166
Eight counts,
murder in the first degree,

31:37.233 --> 31:38.533
four counts,
attempted murder,

31:38.600 --> 31:40.834
illegal possession
of a firearm.

31:40.900 --> 31:43.533
Sentence: life imprisonment

31:43.600 --> 31:45.367
without the possibility
of parole.

31:45.967 --> 31:49.333
- Nikolai Stanislofsky,
Yuri Kosygin.

31:49.400 --> 31:52.433
- [speaking Russian]

31:58.700 --> 32:01.734
[speaking Russian]

32:27.567 --> 32:29.900
Are you here to kill me?

32:35.066 --> 32:38.100
- [speaking Russian]

32:38.667 --> 32:41.300
- Okay.

32:41.367 --> 32:43.400
According to your
work assignment,

32:43.467 --> 32:45.700
you're to be here in the library
from noon till three

32:45.767 --> 32:49.266
helping out the librarian,
you know...

32:53.233 --> 32:55.867
rearranging books
on the shelf.

32:55.934 --> 32:58.033
You're also to take the
book cart to the hospital ward

32:58.100 --> 33:00.500
and the AIDS ward, Unit E.

33:00.567 --> 33:06.367
Hey, Kosygin.

33:06.433 --> 33:07.600
You understanding
any of this?

33:08.967 --> 33:10.800
- Yes.

33:10.867 --> 33:13.834
- Well, breathe or something
every once in a while.

33:17.533 --> 33:20.500
Sit over there until
Mrs. Hubble comes back.

33:26.000 --> 33:29.233
- Hey, you're Kosygin, right?

33:29.300 --> 33:30.734
Yeah. And I heard of you,

33:30.800 --> 33:33.467
The most brutal hitter
in Little Odessa.

33:33.533 --> 33:36.667
Antonio Nappa.

33:36.734 --> 33:39.667
I'm extending my hand
to you in friendship.

33:39.734 --> 33:41.567
- I don't need
your friendship.

33:41.633 --> 33:44.400
- Fine.

33:44.467 --> 33:46.500
Let me tell you something.

33:46.567 --> 33:48.100
My boys control
everything that goes

33:48.166 --> 33:49.500
in and out of this joint.

33:49.567 --> 33:51.200
Drugs, cigarettes, gambling.

33:51.266 --> 33:53.500
You decide to start
your bullshit here,

33:53.567 --> 33:56.600
you won't live
till morning.

33:56.667 --> 34:01.533
- You Italians...
so melodramatic.

34:04.000 --> 34:05.700
- Hey.

34:05.767 --> 34:07.066
- Yes?

34:07.133 --> 34:08.900
- Got word
from Mr. Nappa.

34:08.967 --> 34:10.700
Your pal, uh,
what's his name,

34:10.767 --> 34:12.533
needs to learn
a little respect.

34:12.600 --> 34:14.967
- Kosygin is
no pal of mine.

34:15.033 --> 34:17.600
I'm a Jew, he's Cossack.

34:17.667 --> 34:21.567
In my community,
he's feared for his savagery.

34:21.633 --> 34:23.734
[speaking Russian]

34:23.800 --> 34:26.000
You Sicilians
think you're so tough.

34:26.066 --> 34:29.667
He would cut out your heart,
eat it and not think twice.

34:33.367 --> 34:36.667
- Yeah, well,
you better talk to him

34:36.734 --> 34:38.233
before I do.

34:45.767 --> 34:47.300
[gate buzzes]

34:51.934 --> 34:54.567
- So what do you think?

34:54.633 --> 34:55.800
- About what?

34:55.867 --> 34:58.233
- The new guy, Kosygin.

34:58.300 --> 35:00.633
I tried to chat
with him during dinner.

35:00.700 --> 35:02.934
He sat there frozen
like the tundra.

35:03.500 --> 35:06.100
He scares the living shit
out of me.

35:06.166 --> 35:07.734
- Me, too.

35:11.967 --> 35:13.734
- Lights out!
[gate buzzes]

35:17.767 --> 35:19.867
[indistinct chatter]

35:22.734 --> 35:26.133
[gate buzzes]

35:30.900 --> 35:31.934
- What you got there,
Busmalis?

35:32.000 --> 35:34.400
- I wrote Miss Sally
a fan letter.

35:34.467 --> 35:36.633
Oh, my God, look!

35:36.700 --> 35:39.100
- Wow!
- Fucking thing's autographed.

35:39.166 --> 35:40.934
- They're fake.
- What?

35:41.000 --> 35:42.166
- They're fake,
the autographs.

35:42.233 --> 35:43.166
They're done by a machine.

35:43.233 --> 35:46.433
- Yeah, how do you know that?

35:46.500 --> 35:48.233
- All right, Miss Sally's
may be real,

35:48.300 --> 35:50.767
but not the puppets,
especially not Nooter.

35:50.834 --> 35:53.100
- Why not?
- He's got no hands.

35:53.166 --> 35:54.500
I mean,
how's he going to write?

35:54.567 --> 35:55.934
- With his mouth.

35:56.000 --> 35:57.400
I mean, if he can
swing a mallet with his mouth,

35:57.467 --> 35:59.100
he can certainly
write with it.

35:59.166 --> 36:00.967
- There's a letter.

36:01.033 --> 36:02.834
"Dear Agamemnon,
thank you for writing.

36:02.900 --> 36:05.133
"Nooter, Pecky, and I
are happy, happy, happy

36:05.200 --> 36:06.500
"that you like our show.

36:06.567 --> 36:08.567
Keep watching,
Miss Sally."

36:08.633 --> 36:10.767
- [laughs]
- Form letter.

36:10.834 --> 36:12.166
- Keller, you're
a cynical bastard.

36:12.233 --> 36:14.333
- Hey, you think Miss Sally
sits and reads

36:14.400 --> 36:16.567
every piece
of mail she gets?

36:16.633 --> 36:18.100
With a rack like that,

36:18.166 --> 36:19.500
she's got to be getting
a million letters a day, man.

36:19.567 --> 36:20.900
They got some secretary
sending that shit out.

36:20.967 --> 36:22.800
- No, really? No.

36:22.867 --> 36:24.800
- Hey, look,
live in your fantasy world.

36:24.867 --> 36:27.100
What the hell
do I care?

36:27.166 --> 36:28.767
- I got an idea.

36:28.834 --> 36:32.800
We should write Miss Sally
and ask her to come visit.

36:32.867 --> 36:34.133
- Visit?

36:34.200 --> 36:36.066
Sorry, bro, Miss Sally
ain't coming to Oz.

36:36.133 --> 36:37.567
- She might. Who knows?

36:37.633 --> 36:41.467
I'll write her. Now.

36:41.533 --> 36:43.333
- Man, I'd still
like to fuck her.

36:43.834 --> 36:48.367
- I wouldn't mind a four-way
with Nooter and Pecky.

36:48.433 --> 36:49.600
- What?
[beeping]

36:49.667 --> 36:51.533
- Visiting hours!

36:51.600 --> 36:52.967
- I gotta go
see my family.

36:53.033 --> 36:55.333
- Man, your people
don't quit, huh?

36:55.400 --> 36:56.633
But that's okay, bro,

36:56.700 --> 36:58.333
as long as they keep
bringing them goodies.

36:58.400 --> 36:59.967
- No shit.

37:00.033 --> 37:01.233
- You know, one of these days
I'm going to have to tag along

37:01.300 --> 37:03.967
just to thank
your moms myself, okay?

37:04.233 --> 37:05.600
[gate buzzing]

37:05.667 --> 37:08.600
[percussive music]

37:08.667 --> 37:11.934
♪ ♪

37:12.000 --> 37:14.467
- Where's Papi?

37:17.133 --> 37:18.667
What happened?

37:20.633 --> 37:21.734
What happened?

37:21.800 --> 37:24.667
- Papi had a stroke.

37:24.734 --> 37:28.033
- A stroke?
When?

37:28.100 --> 37:30.300
- Two nights ago,
at home.

37:30.367 --> 37:32.667
Mami was off
from work, thank God.

37:32.734 --> 37:34.834
He's in intensive care.

37:34.900 --> 37:37.767
- Shit. But he's
gonna make it.

37:37.834 --> 37:39.367
- Well, they're doing
what they can.

37:39.433 --> 37:43.033
That's what
the doctor said.

37:50.700 --> 37:54.967
- I--I called him the other day
to say sorry.

37:55.033 --> 37:56.800
- For what?

37:56.867 --> 38:01.100
- Cursing Isabella.

38:01.166 --> 38:05.000
But before
I could it--

38:05.066 --> 38:10.166
we started talking
about something else.

38:10.233 --> 38:12.233
Something stupid.

38:12.300 --> 38:14.400
What was it?
God damn it, what was it?

38:14.467 --> 38:18.700
- Don't worry about it.
- No, I can't remember!

38:18.767 --> 38:21.367
I called to say sorry,
but before I could,

38:21.433 --> 38:25.133
he asked me something first
and I--I-- fuck!

38:25.200 --> 38:27.734
- Keep it down,
Ricardo.

38:29.533 --> 38:31.700
- Carlo.

38:31.767 --> 38:35.867
Carlo.

38:35.934 --> 38:38.266
- Did he say anything to you
guys after the last visit?

38:38.333 --> 38:40.200
- About what?

38:40.266 --> 38:41.967
- The stuff I said.

38:42.033 --> 38:43.800
Was he mad?
- Carlo, it's okay,

